menu "WiFi Station"

    config WIFI_STA_MAX_RETRY
        int "Maximum connection retry attempts before giving up"
        default 10
        range 1 50
        help
            Number of times the WiFi station will attempt to reconnect
            after a disconnection event before logging a fatal error
            and rebooting. Each retry waits WIFI_STA_RETRY_DELAY_MS
            milliseconds before the next attempt.


    config WIFI_STA_ABSOLUTE_TIMEOUT_MINUTES
        int "Absolute disconnection ceiling before portal fallback (minutes)"
        default 30
        range 5 480
        help
            Maximum time (in minutes) the device will stay in a disconnected
            state within a single boot session before treating the situation
            as unresolvable. When this ceiling is hit the device increments
            a persistent reboot-strike counter in NVS and restarts. If the
            strike counter reaches WIFI_STA_ABSOLUTE_TIMEOUT_MAX_REBOOTS the
            device erases credentials and reboots into the provisioning portal.
            The timer restarts fresh on each boot; it does NOT accumulate
            across reboots.

    config WIFI_STA_ABSOLUTE_TIMEOUT_MAX_REBOOTS
        int "Maximum reboot cycles before erasing credentials (reboot-strike threshold)"
        default 7
        range 1 20
        help
            Number of consecutive 30-minute (WIFI_STA_ABSOLUTE_TIMEOUT_MINUTES)
            reboot cycles that must elapse before the device concludes the
            network configuration is permanently broken and erases credentials
            to force re-provisioning. At the default values (30 min × 7 = 210
            min ≈ 3.5 hours) the device gives genuine outages plenty of time to
            resolve on their own. The counter resets to zero the moment a
            successful IP address is obtained. Analogous to WIFI_STA_MAX_RETRY
            for the slow path.

endmenu
